index 0000000..9ad7120
--- /dev/null
+++ b/SOLUTION.md
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# Solution
+
+Two bugs in `lrucache/cache.py`:
+
+1. **`get` didn't refresh recency.** The docstring promises that both `get`
+   and `put` count as a "use", but `get` only read the value — it never called
+   `move_to_end`. This made LRU eviction effectively FIFO-by-insertion, since
+   reading a key never protected it from eviction (`test_get_refreshes_recency`
+   failed). Fix: call `self._data.move_to_end(key)` before returning a
+   non-expired value.
+
+2. **`put` evicted on update-in-place.** The capacity check
+   `len(self._data) >= self.capacity` fired even when `key` already existed in
+   the cache, so overwriting an existing key's value (which doesn't grow the
+   dict) still evicted the least-recently-used entry, incorrectly kicking out
+   an unrelated key (`test_updating_existing_key_does_not_evict_others`
+   failed). Fix: only evict when the key is new —
+   `if key not in self._data and len(self._data) >= self.capacity`.
